<div class="row couple-project" id="couple-project-div">
  <div class="large-6 columns">
    <h3>Our Project</h3>
    <p>
      The Home-Based Care Program is a 21-day seminar to train community health workers in rural Tanzania  on a variety of health topics, with a focus on HIV prevention, care and treatment.
    </p>

    <div class="text-center learn-more"><a href="" class="button small" data-reveal-id="js-learn-more-modal">Learn More</a></div>
    <div id="js-learn-more-modal" class="reveal-modal small medium learn-more-modal" data-reveal>
      <a href="#" class="close-reveal-modal">&times;</a>

      <p>The Wangama dispensary is fortunate to have a village doctor, a midwife, and two nurses on staff who are able to support villagers with basic medications and health counseling. Once constructed, the new ward will enable HIV patients to receive antiretroviral medications, have their CD4 count checked, and receive general counseling--including nutrition and sexual health--with a physician.
      <br />
      <br />
      The closest clinic to Wangama is a 5-6 hour round-trip walk from the village, a tiring hike that requires at least one missed day of farming.  As such, many people living with HIV/AIDS  from Wangama opt out of the journey to the nearest clinic.  Let's help bring the clinic to them so they are more likely to get the medical attention they require and deserve!  
      </p>

    </div>

    <h3>Thanks To <span>You</span>, This Project is: </h3>
